Antiocho] He was a formidable enemy, bold, active, and possessed of immense re- sources. He was defeated (nc. 190) near Magnesia at the foot of Sipylus. L. Scipio had a triumph for his victory and the title Asiaticus. In this war his brother, Publius, surnamed Africanus, who defeated Hannibal at Zama, served as a legatus under Lucius, after Roman fashion.—‘ [si qua] parta :' ‘ aequiparata,’ Madvig, Halm.
